# Documentation Standards

## API Documentation
- Use OpenAPI/Swagger for interactive API documentation
- Document each endpoint with:
  - HTTP method and URL
  - Request parameters and body schema
  - Response schema for success and error cases
  - Example requests and responses
- Include authentication requirements

## README Documentation
- Structure README.md with:
  - Project overview and purpose
  - Features and capabilities
  - Installation and setup instructions
  - Environment configuration
  - API usage examples with curl commands
  - Development workflow
  - Testing procedures
  - Deployment instructions

## Code Documentation
- Use JSDoc comments for functions and classes
- Document parameters, return values, and thrown exceptions
- Include usage examples for complex functions
- Explain non-obvious implementation details

## Architecture Documentation
- Create component diagrams showing:
  - System components and their relationships
  - Request flow through the application
  - Data flow and storage
- Document directory structure and file organization
- Explain design decisions and trade-offs

## AWS Deployment Documentation
- Document AWS resources required
- Include deployment instructions
- Provide troubleshooting guides
- Document monitoring and alerting setup
- Include rollback procedures

## Operation Runbooks
- Create procedures for common operational tasks:
  - Deployment process
  - Monitoring and alerting
  - Backup and restore
  - Troubleshooting common issues
- Document escalation paths and contact information
